egregious use of color (uses 256-color term support):<p>function hl() {
  local R='';
  while [ $# -gt 0 ]; do
    R="$R|$1";
    shift;
  done;
  env GREP_COLORS="mt=38;5;$((RANDOM%256))" egrep --color=always $R;
}<p>then do e.g.<p>whatever pipeline | hl foo bar baz | hl quux | hl '^.* frob.*$' | less -R<p>results in foo/bar/baz highlighted in one color, quux in another, and whole lines containing frob in another.  hopefully the colors aren't indistinguishable from each other or from the terminal background :\<p>I use a somewhat similar setup in emacs, where a key binding adds the word under point to a syntax highlighting table, but the color is computed as the first 6 characters of the md5sum of the word.
